graphsDSESIUCLM

Class TreeMapGraph<V,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • graphsDSESIUCLM.TreeMapGraph<V,E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Graph<V,E>

    public class TreeMapGraph<V,E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Graph<V,E>
    This class implements the interface Graph. Associative containers in the form of treeMaps are used to represent the set of vertices and edges. Therefore, locating or deleting edges and nodes are guarenteed to be done in logarithmic time.
    Version:
    November 2014
    Author:
    Alfonso Niño, Camelia Muñoz-Caro, Crescencio Bravo

      • insertVertex

        public Vertex<V> insertVertex(V e)
        This method inserts a vertex in the graph storing element e. If the graph already contains a vertex with the ID corresponding to the element e no new vertex is added. If no vertex stores an element with the same ID than e, a new vertex is created and added.
        Specified by:
        insertVertex in interface Graph<V,E>
        Parameters:
        e - The element to store in the vertex.
        Returns:
        The vertex stored in the graph that contains element e.

      • insertEdge

        public Edge<E> insertEdge(Vertex<V> u,
                 Vertex<V> v,
                 E e)
        This method inserts an edge in the graph, defined by vertex u and v and storing element e. If the graph already contains an edge with the ID corresponding to the element e no new edge is added. If no edge stores an element with the same ID than e, a new edge is created and added.

        This method allows to add multiple edges between two vertices by using a different ID for each one.

        Specified by:
        insertEdge in interface Graph<V,E>
        Parameters:
        u - The first node defining the edge
        v - The second node defining the edge
        e - The element stored in the edge
        Returns:
        The edge stored in the graph that contains element e

      • insertEdge

        public Edge<E> insertEdge(Element u,
                 Element v,
                 E e)
        Inserts an edge in the graph, defined by elements u and v (for the vertices) and storing e in the edge. If the graph already contains an edge with the key corresponding to the element e no new edge is added. If no edge stores an element with the same key than e, a new adge is created and added. If one of the nodes used to define the edge does not exist in the graph it is created and inserted.
        Specified by:
        insertEdge in interface Graph<V,E>
        Parameters:
        u - Element defining the first node used to define the edge
        v - Element defining the second node used to define the edge
        e - The element to store in the edge
        Returns:
        The edge created

      • insertEdge

        public Edge<E> insertEdge(Vertex<V> u,
                 Vertex<V> v)
        This method inserts an edge in the graph defined by vertex u and v. The ID of the new edge is a string obtained as: u.getID()+"-"+v.getID() + an unique integer labeling that edge.

        Notice that multiple edges between two nodes can be added in this way since all the edges would have different ID.

        Specified by:
        insertEdge in interface Graph<V,E>
        Parameters:
        u - The first node defining the edge
        v - The second node defining the edge
        Returns:
        The edge stored in the graph
